<p class="doc">
    If all you've ever used is Ubuntu, you wouldn't be getting a total view of Linux, CentOS is an alternative distribution of LInux built on Redhat(instead of Debian)  Debian and Redhat do many of the basic Linux tasks in different ways.  They use different package managers and slightly different file layouts.  If you were to only have experience with one, you might feel a little lost the first time you tried to use the other(when apt-get did not work).  Fedora is a good end-user version of Redhat Linux, and CentOS is a production version one that is used by companies in datacenters.

